    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "2 Nephi",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 12,
        "summary": "Isaiah sees the latter-day temple, gathering of Israel, and millennial judgment and peace\u2014The proud and wicked will be brought low at the Second Coming\u2014Compare Isaiah 2. About 559\u2013545\u00a0B.C.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The word that Isaiah, the son of Amoz, saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 2:1 (1\u201322).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it shall come to pass in the last days, when the mountain of the Lord's house shall be established in the top of the mountains, and shall be exalted above the hills, and all nations shall flow unto it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Comparison with the King James Bible in English shows that there are differences in more than half of the 433 verses of Isaiah quoted in the Book of Mormon, while about 200 verses have the same wording as KJV.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Zion.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 24:1.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 49:26; D&C 49:25; 109:61; 133:31 (29\u201331).",
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 130
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And many people shall go and say, Come ye, and let us go up to the mountain of the Lord, to the house of the God of Jacob; and he will teach us of his ways, and we will walk in his paths; for out of Zion shall go forth the law, and the word of the Lord from Jerusalem.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 8:22.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Joel 2:1; 2\u00a0Ne. 30:15 (12\u201318); D&C 133:13.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 122:1.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 101
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 169,
                        "end": 173
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he shall judge among the nations, and shall rebuke many people: and they shall beat their swords into plow-shares, and their spears into pruning-hooks\u2014nation shall not lift up sword against nation, neither shall they learn war any more.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 21:3 (2\u20135, 9).",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O house of Jacob, come ye and let us walk in the light of the Lord; yea, come, for ye have all gone astray, every one to his wicked ways.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 28:14; Mosiah 14:6; Alma 5:37.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 106
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 53:6.",
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore, O Lord, thou hast forsaken thy people, the house of Jacob, because they be replenished from the east, and hearken unto soothsayers like the Philistines, and they please themselves in the children of strangers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sorcery.",
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 141
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 10:14.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 162
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Their land also is full of silver and gold, neither is there any end of their treasures; their land is also full of horses, neither is there any end of their chariots.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Their land is also full of idols; they worship the work of their own hands, that which their own fingers have made.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 2:28. TG\u00a0Idolatry.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the mean man boweth not down, and the great man humbleth himself not, therefore, forgive him not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 34:8; Isa. 2:9.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0unto God; he worships idols instead.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O ye wicked ones, enter into the rock, and hide thee in the dust, for the fear of the Lord and the glory of his majesty shall smite thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 9:3; Rev. 6:15 (15\u201316); Alma 12:14.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it shall come to pass that the lofty looks of man shall be humbled, and the haughtiness of men shall be bowed down, and the Lord alone shall be exalted in that day.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 15:15 (15\u201316).",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the day of the Lord of Hosts soon cometh upon all nations, yea, upon every one; yea, upon the proud and lofty, and upon every one who is lifted up, and he shall be brought low.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Day of the Lord.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 40:11; Mal. 4:1; 2\u00a0Ne. 23:11; D&C 64:24.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 82
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, and the day of the Lord shall come upon all the cedars of Lebanon, for they are high and lifted up; and upon all the oaks of Bashan;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 37:24; Ezek. 31:3; Zech. 11:1 (1\u20132).",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And upon all the high mountains, and upon all the hills, and upon all the nations which are lifted up, and upon every people;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 30:25.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And upon every high tower, and upon every fenced wall;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 21:15 (15, 18).",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And upon all the ships of the sea, and upon all the ships of Tarshish, and upon all pleasant pictures.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "The Greek (Septuagint) has \u201cships of the sea.\u201d The Hebrew has \u201cships of Tarshish.\u201d The Book of Mormon has both, showing that the brass plates had lost neither phrase.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the loftiness of man shall be bowed down, and the haughtiness of men shall be made low; and the Lord alone shall be exalted in that day.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Haughtiness.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0the day of the Lord's coming in glory; see vv.\u00a017\u201321.",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 139
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the idols he shall utterly abolish.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they shall go into the holes of the rocks, and into the caves of the earth, for the fear of the Lord shall come upon them and the glory of his majesty shall smite them, when he ariseth to shake terribly the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Glory of.",
                        "start": 134,
                        "end": 139
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In that day a man shall cast his idols of silver, and his idols of gold, which he hath made for himself to worship, to the moles and to the bats;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To go into the clefts of the rocks, and into the tops of the ragged rocks, for the fear of the Lord shall come upon them and the majesty of his glory shall smite them, when he ariseth to shake terribly the earth.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Cease ye from man, whose breath is in his nostrils; for wherein is he to be accounted of?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}